procedures.name: Venipuncture
procedures.label: Blood Draw
procedures.description: Collection of venous blood samples for laboratory analysis, including pharmacokinetics (PK), pharmacodynamics (PD), hematology, clinical chemistry, serology, HbA1c, serum pregnancy test, FSH, and genetic analysis.

code.decode: Collection of venous blood by venipuncture

procedures.name: Urine Sample Collection
procedures.label: Urine Test
procedures.description: Collection of urine for urinalysis, urine pregnancy test, and urine drug screen.

procedures.name: Intravenous Insulin Infusion
procedures.label: Insulin Infusion
procedures.description: Administration of intravenous insulin to induce a controlled state of hypoglycemia.

procedures.name: Nasal Glucagon Administration
procedures.label: Nasal Glucagon
procedures.description: Administration of LY900018, a powder formulation of human glucagon, via a single-use nasal dosing device.

procedures.name: Intramuscular Glucagon Injection
procedures.label: IM Glucagon
procedures.description: Administration of reconstituted glucagon (GlucaGen) via intramuscular injection.

procedures.name: Vital Signs Monitoring
procedures.label: Vital Signs
procedures.description: Measurement of supine blood pressure, pulse rate, and body temperature at specified time points.

procedures.name: Electrocardiogram
procedures.label: ECG
procedures.description: Recording of single and triplicate 12-lead ECGs to monitor cardiac activity.

procedures.name: Bedside Plasma Glucose Monitoring
procedures.label: Bedside PG
procedures.description: Frequent monitoring of plasma glucose levels at the bedside for safety during hypoglycemia induction and post-treatment.

procedures.name: Physical Examination
procedures.label: Physical Exam
procedures.description: A medical examination performed at screening to assess patient eligibility.

procedures.name: Height and Weight Measurement
procedures.label: Height/Weight
procedures.description: Measurement of patient's height at screening and weight before procedures.

procedures.name: Injection-Site Assessment
procedures.label: Injection Site Check
procedures.description: Assessment of the injection site for patients receiving intramuscular glucagon (IMG).

procedures.name: Nasal Inspection
procedures.label: Nasal Exam
procedures.description: Inspection of the nasal passages for patients receiving either IMG or LY900018.

procedures.name: Edinburgh Hypoglycemia Scale
procedures.label: Hypoglycemia Questionnaire
procedures.description: Administration of a questionnaire to evaluate the recovery from clinical symptoms of hypoglycemia.

medicalDevices.name: Nasal Dosing Device
medicalDevices.label: Nasal Glucagon Device
medicalDevices.description: A user-friendly, single-use, nasal dosing device that delivers 3 mg glucagon powder (LY900018).

medicalDevices.name: Injection Kit (Vial and Syringe)
medicalDevices.label: Glucagon Kit
medicalDevices.description: Kit for intramuscular glucagon (GlucaGen) which requires reconstitution of glucagon powder before administration via injection.

medicalDevices.name: IV Infusion System
medicalDevices.label: IV Infusion
medicalDevices.description: System used for the intravenous infusion of insulin to induce hypoglycemia.

medicalDevices.name: Bedside Glucose Meter
medicalDevices.label: Glucose Meter
medicalDevices.description: Device for bedside monitoring of plasma glucose (PG) levels for safety.

medicalDevices.name: 12-lead ECG Machine
medicalDevices.label: ECG Machine
medicalDevices.description: Device used to perform single and triplicate 12-lead electrocardiograms.

medicalDevices.name: Continuous Subcutaneous Insulin Infusion Pump
medicalDevices.label: CSII Pump
medicalDevices.description: An insulin pump used by some patients for their daily insulin therapy.
